Biography

2017:

• Finished 16th in program history in points (31 points)

• Tied for 17th in school history in goals (10 goals)

Appeared in 22 games and made 11 starts...scored two goals against Maine on Aug. 27...added a goal against Dartmouth on Sept. 15...notched her fourth goal of the season at Elon on Oct. 8...assisted on Lizzie George's game-winning goal in the CAA semifinals vs. Drexel on Nov. 3.

2016: Appeared in all 22 games and made eight starts...tallied three goals and three assists...posted two assists in the Huskies' victory over Holy Cross on Sept. 8...scored a goal against Boston University on Sept. 15...netted the game-winning goal in a win over the College of Charleston on Oct. 2...scored her third goal of the season against Hofstra on Oct. 15...assisted on Hannah Rosenblatt's goal in a 2-0 shutout of Towson on Oct. 21.

2015: Appeared in all 20 games and made eight starts...finished fifth on the team with nine points on three goals and three assists...scored her first collegiate goal, the game-winning goal, in the 32nd minute of a 3-1 win at Furman on Aug. 23...assisted on Mackenzie Dowd's overtime game-winner against St. Joseph's on Aug. 28...posted a goal and an assist in a 6-1 win at UMass Lowell on Aug. 30...scored for the second straight game with a 64th-minute strike against Boston University on Sept. 3...assisted on Hannah Lopiccolo's 69th minute goal against Maine on Sept. 6.

2014: Appeared in 22 games and made 10 starts...posted four assists, including three on game-winning goals...assisted on Mackenzie Dowd's goal in a 4-0 win at Maine on Sept. 7...assisted on Carina Deandreis' game-winner vs. Albany on Sept. 21...assisted on Lahaina Zoller's game-winner against Towson on Oct. 3...assisted on Zoller's game-winner for the second straight game on Oct. 5 vs. James Madison...had the shot that led to the game-winning own-goal by Boston University in NU's 2-0 win in the NCAA tournament first round on Nov. 15.

Before NU: Played four years varsity soccer at Toms River High School North, earning Offensive MVP her senior season...won Shore conference champions 2013...also ran four years varsity track.

Personal: Mother ran track for Appalachian State University...plans to major in English at Northeastern.
